---
description: Core context and operating model for the NestJS backend foundation starter
alwaysApply: true
---

- Read `AGENTS.md` before planning or editing code.
- This repository is a reusable NestJS starter kit, not a single-purpose application.
- Preserve API, Worker, Cron and Migrations as independently deployable entrypoints.
- Use npm and the versions declared in `package.json`.
- Work on one backlog issue at a time unless the user explicitly approves a combined scope.
- Prefer local, backward-compatible changes over broad rewrites.
- Treat documentation as a baseline to verify, not as automatic proof of runtime behavior.
- Never report success without listing the commands that were actually executed and their results.
